text: Magnolia Mills, also known as Innes Elevator Mills, was a historic grist mill complex located at Warrensburg, Johnson County, Missouri. The original building was built in 1879, and enlarged in 1884, 1888, and 1918. It consisted of a four-story, frame mill building with a three-story frame elevator topped with a monitor roof and large cupola. A modern concrete elevator and mill were added in the late-1940s. (includes 14 photographs from 1996) Only the concrete elevator remains of the original buildings. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1996. ==References== Category:Grinding mills on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Industrial buildings completed in 1879 Category:Buildings and structures in Johnson County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Johnson County, Missouri
